{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:10:20.582Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "One-Cycle — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What One-Cycle Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "One-Cycle (1Cycle)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a learning rate scheduling policy introduced by Leslie Smith in 2018 that performs "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "one complete cycle"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of learning rate from low to high and back to very low."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The policy alternates between two distinct phases:\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increasing phase"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning rate starts low and rises to a peak value (η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "max)\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "Decreasing phase"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": ": Learning rate gradually decreases to a very low value"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This approach accelerates convergence by up to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "10x compared to traditional schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": " like constant or exponentially decaying rates."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why One-Cycle Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle remains one of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "most effective techniques"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for optimizing model training in 2025, with significant benefits:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Peak accuracy in fewer epochs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All deep learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improved generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoids sharp local minima"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vision models, object detection"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scalability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works with large batch sizes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LLMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High LR acts as regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduced training time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Significantly fewer epochs needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Production training"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In 2024, One-Cycle has been successfully applied to deep architectures and large batch sizes, yielding both speed and accuracy improvements."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How One-Cycle Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Two Phases"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LR\nη_max |       /\\\n      |      /  \\\n      |     /    \\\n      |    /      \\\n      |   /        \\\n η_min|  /          \\______\n      |/                  \\\n      +---------------------→ Epoch\n      0   50%     100%"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Phase 1: Increasing Learning Rate (First 50%)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Starts at lower learning rate (1/5th or 1/10th of max)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linearly increases"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to peak value (η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "max)\n- Promotes rapid exploration of loss landscape\n- Avoids sharp local minima"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Phase 2: Decreasing Learning Rate (Last 50%)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Gradually decreases from η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "max to very low value\n- Enables fine-tuning of parameters\n- Converges on smoother, more generalizable solutions\n- Annihilates LR way below minimum (1/10th or 1/100th) for final iterations"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Momentum Cycling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle also involves "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cycling momentum inversely with learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning Rate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (exploration)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth convergence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (fine-tuning)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents overfitting"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This combination helps maintain smooth convergence and prevents overfitting, making it especially effective for larger learning rates in the exploratory phase."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setting Hyperparameters"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-Step Guide"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Choose maximum LR using Learning Rate Finder"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Use LR Finder to find optimal η"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "max - Test range: 1e-5 to 10, find where loss drops"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Set minimum LR"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Minimum = 1/5th or 1/10th of maximum LR - Example: max=0.1 → min=0.01"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Set annealing LR"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Annealing LR = 10/100 times smaller than minimum - Example: min=0.01 → annealing=0.001"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Set cycle length"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Cycle length slightly less than total epochs - Example: 90 epochs for 100 total epochs"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't forget to reset!"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using OneCycleLR"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.optim as optim\nfrom torch.optim.lr_scheduler import OneCycleLR\n\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(10, 1)\noptimizer = optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=0.01)\n\n# One-Cycle scheduler\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(\n    optimizer,\n    max_lr=0.1,              # Peak learning rate [web:207]\n    min_lr=0.001,            # Minimum learning rate [web:207]\n    epochs=100,              # Total epochs [web:207]\n    steps_per_epoch=50,      # Batches per epoch [web:207]\n    phase1_epochs=50,        # First 50% (increasing) [web:207]\n    phase2_epochs=50,        # Last 50% (decreasing) [web:207]\n)\n\n# Training loop - step after EVERY batch\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    for batch_idx, (data, target) in enumerate(train_loader):\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        output = model(data)\n        loss = torch.nn.MSELoss()(output, target)\n        loss.backward()\n        optimizer.step()\n        \n        scheduler.step()  # Call after batch [web:207]\n    \n    lr = scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]\n    print(f\"Epoch {epoch}, LR: {lr}\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key detail"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " should be called after "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "every batch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not every epoch."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With Momentum Cycling"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "optimizer = optim.SGD(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=0.01,\n    momentum=0.9\n)\n\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(\n    optimizer,\n    max_lr=0.1,\n    min_lr=0.001,\n    epochs=100,\n    steps_per_epoch=50,\n    momentum_phases=(0.85, 0.95)  # Momentum: low→high [web:207]\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\nimport numpy as np\n\ntotal_steps = 5000  # epochs * steps_per_epoch\n\ndef one_cycle_schedule(step):\n    \"\"\"One-Cycle learning rate schedule\"\"\"\n    max_lr = 0.1\n    min_lr = 0.001\n    anneal_lr = 0.0001\n    cycle_steps = 4500  # Slightly less than total\n    \n    if step < cycle_steps / 2:\n        # Phase 1: Increasing\n        progress = step / (cycle_steps / 2)\n        return min_lr + (max_lr - min_lr) * progress\n    elif step < cycle_steps:\n        # Phase 2: Decreasing (linear)\n        progress = (step - cycle_steps / 2) / (cycle_steps / 2)\n        return max_lr - (max_lr - anneal_lr) * progress\n    else:\n        # Final annealing\n        return anneal_lr\n\nlr_schedule = tf.keras.optimizers.schedules.PiecewiseConstantDecay(\n    boundaries=list(range(total_steps)),\n    values=[one_cycle_schedule(i) for i in range(total_steps)]\n)\n\noptimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr_schedule)\n\nmodel.fit(train_data, train_labels, epochs=100, steps_per_epoch=50, optimizer=optimizer)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle vs. Other Schedules"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cosine Annealing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Warmup + Cosine"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step Decay"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Shape"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ramp up + down"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth cosine"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Warmup + cosine"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Staircase"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Up to 10x faster"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exploration"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High LR phase"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High LR acts as reg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tuning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate (need LR Finder)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Easy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vision, object detection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LLMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vision"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use One-Cycle"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best Use Cases:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Object detection"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (SGD+momentum+damped One-Cycle is robust)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computer vision"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (ResNet, CNNs)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large batch training"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (>1000)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When you need fastest convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (up to 10x faster)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When using SGD with momentum"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When Not to Use:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive optimizers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Adam/AdamW): Modern adaptive optimizers are \"REALLY good in nailing early training\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Linear warmup + cosine decay is \"a little more principled\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quick experiments"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Need LR Finder for max_lr tuning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning Rate Finder (Essential for One-Cycle)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Find Max LR"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def lr_finder(model, optimizer, train_loader, max_lr=10, steps=100):\n    \"\"\"Find optimal maximum learning rate\"\"\"\n    losses = []\n    lrs = []\n    \n    lr = 1e-5\n    for i, (data, target) in enumerate(train_loader):\n        if i >= steps:\n            break\n        \n        # Update LR\n        lr = lr * max_lr ** (1/steps)\n        for param_group in optimizer.param_groups:\n            param_group['lr'] = lr\n        \n        # Train\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        output = model(data)\n        loss = torch.nn.MSELoss()(output, target)\n        loss.backward()\n        optimizer.step()\n        \n        losses.append(loss.item())\n        lrs.append(lr)\n    \n    # Plot and find best LR (where loss is lowest)\n    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n    plt.plot(lrs, losses)\n    plt.xlabel('Learning Rate')\n    plt.ylabel('Loss')\n    plt.show()\n    \n    return lrs[np.argmin(losses)]\n\n# Find optimal max_lr\nmax_lr = lr_finder(model, optimizer, train_loader)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Mistakes to Avoid"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake 1: Calling step() After Epoch Instead of Batch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# WRONG: step() after epoch\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    train_epoch()\n    scheduler.step()  # ERROR! [web:207]\n\n# RIGHT: step() after every batch\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    for batch in train_loader:\n        train_batch()\n        scheduler.step()  # Correct [web:207]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake 2: Not Using LR Finder"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# WRONG: Arbitrary max_lr\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(optimizer, max_lr=0.01)  # May be suboptimal\n\n# RIGHT: Use LR Finder\nmax_lr = lr_finder(model, optimizer, train_loader)  # Optimal [web:205]\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(optimizer, max_lr=max_lr)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake 3: Using with Adaptive Optimizers"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# NOT IDEAL: Adaptive optimizers don't need One-Cycle\noptimizer = optim.Adam(...)  # Already handles early training well\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(optimizer, max_lr=0.1)  # Unnecessary\n\n# BETTER: Use with SGD\noptimizer = optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=0.01, momentum=0.9)\nscheduler = OneCycleLR(optimizer, max_lr=0.1)  # Works well [web:208]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of One-Cycle as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "exploring a city then settling down"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rapid exploration"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Phase 1): Drive fast through city, see everything quickly"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High speed"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (high LR): Cover large areas of loss landscape"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Avoid bad areas"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fast exploration skips sharp local minima"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Settle down"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Phase 2): Slow down to find the best neighborhood"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fine-tune"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (low LR): Carefully adjust to find exact best spot"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of One-Cycle momentum cycling as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "driving a car"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High speed (high LR)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use low momentum (less inertia) for quick turns"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low speed (low LR)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use high momentum (more inertia) for smooth driving"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Balance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevents overfitting while maintaining smooth convergence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "One-Cycle"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": One complete cycle from low→high→low learning rate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Introduced"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Leslie Smith, 2018"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Phase 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Linearly increase LR from min to max (first 50%)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Phase 2"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Decrease LR from max to very low (last 50%)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Up to 10x compared to traditional schedules"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Momentum cycling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Inverse with LR (low momentum at high LR, high momentum at low LR)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": High LR acts as regularization, prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Max LR"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Find using Learning Rate Finder (range test)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Min LR"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 1/5th or 1/10th of max LR"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Annealing LR"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 10/100 times smaller than min LR"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "OneCycleLR(optimizer, max_lr=0.1, epochs=100, steps_per_epoch=50)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Call step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": After every batch, not every epoch"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Object detection, computer vision, large batch training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD + momentum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Works exceptionally well with SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for Adam"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adaptive optimizers already handle early training well"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Replaced by warmup + cosine decay (more principled)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-Cycle is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "powerful technique"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for accelerating model training and improving generalization, especially effective with SGD and momentum for vision tasks and object detection, though it's being replaced by warmup + cosine decay for transformers and adaptive optimizers."}]}]}}